post: {'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug legalisation would mean governments get to suggest a recommended dose, preventing the incidence of death by overdose. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'A legalization of all drugs may lead to many [replacing](https://theintercept.com/2018/04/20/marijuana-legalization-alcohol-consumption/) part of their alcohol consumption with healthier drugs. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The cost of alcohol was roughly 3 times higher during prohibition than compared to previous prices \\([pg. 7](http://www.nber.org/papers/w3675.pdf)\\). So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many [deaths](http://www.bbc.com/news/uk-24581947) attributed to ecstasy \\(or MDMA\\) use are actually caused by other, unwanted ingredients.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If government regulations lead to drugs being expensive, it is possible people will still try to access cheaper drugs on a black market and these drugs may still be dangerous or of poor quality. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalization will not drastically affect drug use. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Justifying a ban because it provides people with more autonomy is an inherent contradiction. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In a truly free society self regulation should be our privilege. You are free to not use drugs, and you should be just as free to use them. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "A society where everyone consumes moderate amounts of drugs wouldn't be much different than the societies of today. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is [no mention](https://www.leafly.com/news/cannabis-101/cannabis-and-the-constitution-a-brief-history-of-cannabis-in-the-u-s) of cannabis, nor any other drugs, in the Constitution.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drugs are insanely profitable at a relatively low level of effort, as opposed to other crimes.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue is not drug legalization, but the functioning of the health insurances. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will allow governments to fight addictive drugs more effectively. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legal drugs make it easier for criminals to coerce prostitutes through drug addiction with the state being able to do less to rehabilitate them forcefully. That's why legalization of drugs is a really bad idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The pharmaceutical industry is far less dangerous or violent than the alternative of drug cartels. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There are legal substances which have a much higher toxicity and legal substances which can be developed to be highly toxic. The possible use of drugs as weapons is irrelevant as there are much more dangerous substances freely available.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing drugs would increase the probability of violence and offenses.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is a high level of correlation between [poverty](https://borgenproject.org/addiction-poverty-connected/) and substance abuse.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalising drug use would not significantly increase the consumption of drugs. That's why all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegally acquired date rape drugs could be even more dangerous to victims, as they may be cut with dangerous chemicals. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': '[Psychosis](https://www.earlypsychosis.ca/pages/curious/concerned-safety) can cause the sufferer to carry out self-harm or, in severe cases, suicide. I think drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There are often structurally similar legal compounds which can be researched instead of the illegal variation. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In countries where "snus" is legal, the boxes has a compartment for spent product. This would disincetivized and lead to higher penalties if possession was illegal. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The problems](https://neaddictions.com/the-dangers-of-heroin-addiction/) seen in heroin addicts are primarily caused by complications related to injecting the substance, overdosing and poor quality product, and not the direct effects of the drug on the body.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This is similar to how legal drugs, such as alcohol, are currently treated in most countries: harmful use is punished and use that does not harm others is not. This distinction allows those who use drugs safely to do so without repercussions. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help reduce social rifts.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Following legalisation Canada experienced [shortages of cannabis](https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/canada-marijuana-legal-weed-shortage-pot-running-out-a8593861.html), suggesting that legalisation had caused new individuals to begin using the drug.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Making things safer is always preferable.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'It will destroy jobs for drug enforcement agencies, lawyers, judges, police, prison wardens. There is a whole industry depending on it.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's people's own choice whether to be moral or not. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It's entirely possible for the issue to be intolerance and lack of understanding from the family itself. In those cases, the issue is the reaction of the family, and not the drug use or drug users themselves. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The legalization of drugs deprives criminals of a substantial source of their income. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Dangerous substitute drugs will be contained. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'No alcohol or tobacco company has openly killed anyone to continue selling their product.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "In countries where using marijuana is legal or allowed, [smoking games](https://honestmarijuana.com/weed-games/) have arisen to get more stoned/high more quickly. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Patients will be able to create, combine or grow their own medicines.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This isn't possible with the most popular date rape drug alcohol, at least not in higher doses, as it's taste is quite unmistakable."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Sobriety may be required for the optimal exercise of rational moral agency; however, it is not required for the generell exercise of rational moral agency. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Illegal drug dealers typically require no age verification from their clients. Legal drugs would require ID to buy thus making them harder for teens to aquire. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will help contain the dangerous drug cartels. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Drug prohibition consumes a considerable portion of public spending.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Education and information campaigns could be funded by taxes on the drugs themselves. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Justifying a ban because it provides people with more autonomy is an inherent contradiction. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It is possible that decriminalization dissuades those who specifically start using drugs as a way of breaking the law, such as [early data from Portugal](https://www.leafly.com/news/politics/portugal-drug-decriminalization-statistics) suggests. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The illegality of less addictive alternatives to legally prescribed opioids has been a large factor in the opioid crisis. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, the War on Drugs has led to the [mass incarceration](http://www.drugpolicy.org/issues/race-and-drug-war) of African Americans and other minority groups.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The consumption of psychoactive substances creates religious and transcendental [experiences](https://www.sciencealert.com/how-religion-led-to-humanity-s-love-for-drugs): both are a relevant part of human evolution and significantly shaped human culture. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Once you replace the dealers and kingpins of the neighborhoods whose flashy lifestyle would look appealing to naive kids, drugs would lose some of their appeal. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Science can already study drugs, just with some [constraints](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4307971/). I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'According to [Human Right Watch](https://www.hrw.org/news/2013/06/04/americas-decriminalize-personal-use-drugs), subjecting people to disproportionate criminal sanctions for the personal use of drugs "infringes on their autonomy".'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Or it suggests that by removing the profit motive of banned drugs, the suppliers were less motivated to produce and distribute it.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Laws should be introduced on an entirely pragmatic basis, not on the basis of moral signaling. If legalising drugs reduces harm, this should be sufficient evidence that it is a good policy. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Medical professionals have expressed [negative attitudes](https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23490450) in treating illegal substance abusers, which subsequently negatively impacts their treatment. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "This is similar to how legal drugs, such as alcohol, are currently treated in most countries: harmful use is punished and use that does not harm others is not. This distinction allows those who use drugs safely to do so without repercussions. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'US states that have legalised marijuana have seen a lot of benefits.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Many drugs have a long history of responsible use within their historical context.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It would be more difficult to use to drugs as a mean of coercion if there would be legal ways of obtaining them and no need to hide the use of narcotics as it would no longer be illegal. Prostitutes would not need criminals to gain access to drugs. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Designer drugs already exist, are legal and work this angle. I believe all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Fewer [productive](https://www.houstonchronicle.com/business/outside-the-boardroom/article/Mass-incarceration-hurts-U-S-economy-7434722.php) people will be in jail. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the long run, the standing of the U.S. government did not suffer from ending the Alcohol Prohibition in the 1930s. Any potential reputational damage from ending marijuana or other prohibitions would be fleeting.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Chronic cocaine use causes [multiple damaging health effects](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cocaine#Chronic) to the user, combined with an increased tolerance, leading to a snowball effect of deteriorating health.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Criminalising the activity of drug users has negative effects on individuals, their families, and society. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'People may drive under the influence of drugs or make other decisions with public consequences.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "In the US, incarceration reduces former inmates' earnings by [40 percent](https://www.pewtrusts.org/en/research-and-analysis/reports/0001/01/01/collateral-costs) on average and limits their future economic mobility."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'In the US, as of 2018 there are roughly [235,000](https://www.prisonpolicy.org/reports/pie2018.html) inmates behind bars for drug-related crimes. I think legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legal drugs will likely make it a lot easier for young people to get access to them. So drugs should remain illegal.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even though illegal drugs may still exist if drugs were legalised, there would be far less of them than when illegal drugs were the only option. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Recreational drugs can be used as self medication especially for those with severe mental health issues like PTSD and psychosis.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Incarceration does not treat addiction; the money spent on incarcerated non-violent drug offenders could be instead used to fund addiction treatment.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The issue with these drugs is that it's possible for someone to ingest it unknowingly, after someone dropped them in their drink etc. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "The law regulation of the drug's market will standardize the quality of the products, and their safety, creating incentives for the consumers to prefer to deal in the legal market. I think all drugs should be legal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': '[The problems](https://neaddictions.com/the-dangers-of-heroin-addiction/) seen in heroin addicts are primarily caused by complications related to injecting the substance, overdosing and poor quality product, and not the direct effects of the drug on the body.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The number of deaths from overdose will rise dramatically as a result of easy access to drugs including meth, MDMA, and heroin. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is a false equivalency. Providing a service or good to bolster economic growth is not the same as being forced to give your money to the government.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Driving a car or operating machinery while under the influence of drugs is illegal. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is only a viable strategy for some individuals whom are already close to the legal age, as opposed to a much younger person buying from other young people recruited by the black market.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The US government has [previously supported](https://www.ozy.com/flashback/when-the-government-said-marijuana-made-you-crazy/88232) the claim that marijuana use causes individuals to rape and murder others, or commit suicide. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'The only way to know if the related compound acts the same is by doing the research that was banned in the first place. So legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legalizing marijuana will increase the risk of accidents on the highways \\(and indeed has in [Washington, Oregon and Colorado](http://fortune.com/2018/10/18/legal-marijuana-car-accidents-study/) where it has been legalized\\) causing harm to others.'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'If legalised, drug users could be less likely to leave dangerous paraphernalia \\(broken pipes, syringes, etc.\\) behind in public places as the fear of criminal penalties for the possession of drug paraphernalia would no longer be an issue. This would lessen risk of disease and injury. So all drugs should be legal.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': "Legalizing drugs will not automatically remove the prejudice. If people see those on drugs being violent or a nuisance to society, the prejudice will likely remain. That's why drugs should remain illegal."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legalization will remove the taboo that drug addiction currently carries with it. As a result, addicts will no longer be a target of prejudice. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Legal companies would be able to take over the drugs-related sector from illegal criminal organisations. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It can be argued that the terms 'recreational' and 'medicinal' are interchangeable. So all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Children of drug addicts would have a much higher chance of receiving the appropriate help if drug users did not have to hide.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "They already do this with alcohol or cigarettes, which hasn't caused our society to collapse."}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Even a year after release, former convicts [are 10-18 times more likely](https://sph.unc.edu/sph-news/former-inmates-at-high-risk-for-opioid-overdose-following-prison-release/) to die of an overdose than the average population.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Organized crime would find themselves without a cash-flow and resort to much more violent kidnapping and extortion. So legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'There is [no/little research](https://www.drugabuse.gov/publications/drugfacts/hallucinogens) regarding the long-term effects of hallucinogens. So drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'This is not mutually exclusive with legalizing drugs. Both could be done. I think all drugs should be legal.'}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'The results can be made evident through legal packaging requirements and health campaigns. I think legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'Established entities selling drugs would almost certainly not engage in gun battles on the streets over "[turf](https://www.urbandictionary.com/define.php?term=Turf)".'}

{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Legalizing drugs does not imply you may use them on someone without their permission. It's already illegal to give someone else a narcotic they were not prescribed, even though the drug itself is legal. I think all drugs should be legal."}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'It also means there will be less demand for young people as workers in the black market. I believe legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "Taking a more effective approach is not giving up. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}
{'type': 'con', 'text': 'Legislators should not be supporting or incentivising the use of any drug that leads to hallucinating and or violence. I believe legalization of drugs is a really bad idea.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': "It is unlikely that a low level drug dealer will shift to trafficking human beings the moment drugs get legalised. That's why legalization of drugs is a pretty good idea."}

{'type': 'con', 'text': 'If drugs are legalised, they will not be as expensive as they are now. Estimations of tax revenue based on current prices may be inaccurate. I believe drugs should remain illegal.'}
{'type': 'pro', 'text': 'There is no guarantee that a similar legal compound will act the same way as the original one.'}
